  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat the oven and roast the gnocchi</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Set the oven to</span> 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6. Boil a kettle.</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>gnocchi</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable&nbsp;oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up.</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 minutes or until golden and crispy.</p>\r\n<p>Tip: give the gnocchi a mix halfway through cooking so that they colour evenly.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Infuse the saffron</strong></p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> saffron</strong> and set aside to infuse &ndash; this is your<strong> saffron stock</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate!) the <strong>garlic</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare your saffron sauce </strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a pot with a matching lid with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat.</p>\r\n<p>Once melted, add the <strong>shallot</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 3-4 minutes or until softened.</p>\r\n<p>Once softened, add the<strong> saffron stock</strong> and cook for 1-2 minutes further.</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add cream to your saffron sauce</strong></p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks.</p>\r\n<p>Stir in&nbsp;the <strong>clotted cream</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> and cook for 2-3 minutes or until the sauce has thickened to the consistency of <strong>double cream</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Stir in the juice of 1/4<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1/2]</span><strong> lemon</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; this is your<strong> saffron cream sauce</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into wedges.</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1554.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Stir-fry the<span class=\"text-highlight\"> Tenderstem</span> broccoli</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat.</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">Tenderstem</span>&nbsp;broccoli</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 minutes or until starting to soften.</p>\r\n<p>Add a splash of <strong>water</strong> and cook, covered, for 1-2 minutes further or until&nbsp;tender with a slight bite.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
